The paper proposes a new approach for causal inference in time series data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the method's performance under the additive noise model, which is a common topic in information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
